Debt

* Bank of Montreal is issuing $100 million of 10 percent Eurobonds due 1990 at 101 through Bankers Trust International.

* Associates Corp. of North America, a unit of Gulf & Western Inc., is offering $200 million of 9.70 percent notes due 1997 at 99.90 to yield 9.73 percent through Goldman, Sachs & Co. Noncallable, the notes are rated Aa-3 by Moody's and AA- by S.&P.

* Northern Illinois Gas Co., a unit of Nicor Inc., has filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission for a shelf offering of up to $100 million in first mortgage bonds.

* Pepsico is offering $100 million of floating-rate notes due 1990 at a price of 100 through Morgan Stanley & Co. Interest rates on the notes will be adjusted weekly to eight-tenths of a percentage point more than the yield on three-month Treasury bills. Noncallable, the issue is rated A-1 by Moody's and A+ by S.&P.